	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NES is much easier. For one thing, the Super NES is in effect two different computers with different assembly languages: one for sound and one for everything else, and the communication between the two is slow.
<br />
<br />If you're considering the Super NES, consider developing for the Game Boy Advance instead. It's much easier to get GBA copiers so that you can try your code on the hardware.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


