		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Whether you choose a high level language or low level, your algorithms will be pretty much the same. I don't think there's a real advantage to either. The question is whether or not you want to do a console game or PC game. A PC game will probably be less manageable when written in assembly than a NES game. 
<br />
<br />If you know C, I wouldn't waste time with Python. SDL or Allegro can be set up pretty easily and there are many tutorials out there to get people started with game programming.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


